UK user here.I've been using the unpaid version for a few weeks now for training with my son. I've upgraded to the paid version for the extra customisability, and have no hesitation in highly recommending this app to others :-)

I had the free version and decided to go for the paid one. It's worth it, you can custom set the length of each round, create tons of profiles and it never fails. I use it on my tablet and phone and the text is very visible. Connect this to a Bluetooth speaker or through an aux cable and you basically have a boxing timer like in the gyms.
Best boxing timer ever
I'm able to set up various training session with a special program for each session.

So, I got the free version, set up a bunch of profiles and really came to love the app. I used it a few times, decided to support the developer and went for the paid version. It's the right thing to do and so long to those irritating ads. Unfortunately, when you make the switch from free to paid, your profiles don't come through. That's a lot of tinkering, adjusting and contemplation lost along the way. It's a small point, but a rather relevant one, if you happen to spend a lot of time setting up profiles. Beyond that, this is one fine app. I've experimented with a few, and so far only this one allows you to customize individual rounds so deeply. The option to change the rest time per round is sweet. Good sound options, too, and this is the only app I've come across that has the vintage CLACK, CLACK, CLACK to warn of the final ten seconds of a round. I think the developer should add the voice of Mickey growling, "YOU'RE A TOMATO!" for those days when you just can't get through your heavy bag workouts. Although, the option to add our own sounds is there, so maybe I'll add it myself. Great app.
